          "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"aosp-mirror/platform_frameworks_base\",\n      \"path\": \"core/java/android/app/Activity.java\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"aosp-mirror/platform_frameworks_base\",\n      \"path\": \"core/java/android/app/ActivityThread.java\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"aosp-mirror/platform_frameworks_base\",\n      \"path\": \"services/core/java/com/android/server/wm/ActivityRecord.java\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"aosp-mirror/platform_frameworks_base\",\n      \"path\": \"services/core/java/com/android/server/wm/ActivityTaskManagerService.java\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"aosp-mirror/platform_frameworks_base\",\n      \"path\": \"core/java/android/app/Activity.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Activity\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"aosp-mirror/platform_frameworks_base\",\n      \"path\": \"core/java/android/app/ActivityThread.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"ActivityThread\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"aosp-mirror/platform_frameworks_base\",\n      \"path\": \"services/core/java/com/android/server/wm/ActivityRecord.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"ActivityRecord\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"aosp-mirror/platform_frameworks_base\",\n      \"path\": \"services/core/java/com/android/server/wm/ActivityTaskManagerService.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"ActivityTaskManagerService\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The Android Activity lifecycle is implemented across four key Java source files in the AOSP platform_frameworks_base repository:\\n\\n1. **Activity.java** (core/java/android/app/Activity.java): The base Activity class that extends ContextThemeWrapper. This file defines the public lifecycle callback methods including onCreate(), onStart(), and onResume() that developers override to implement activity-specific behavior.\\n\\n2. **ActivityThread.java** (core/java/android/app/ActivityThread.java): The main thread of an Android application that extends ClientTransactionHandler. This class is responsible for managing the application's main thread and driving lifecycle transitions by executing the lifecycle-related operations on activities.\\n\\n3. **ActivityRecord.java** (services/core/java/com/android/server/wm/ActivityRecord.java): The server-side representation of an Activity (extends WindowToken). This class runs in the system_server process and tracks the state and properties of activities from the system's perspective, including lifecycle state management.\\n\\n4. **ActivityTaskManagerService.java** (services/core/java/com/android/server/wm/ActivityTaskManagerService.java): The system service (extends IActivityTaskManager.Stub) that manages activity stacks and tasks. It coordinates lifecycle transitions for all activities in the system and enforces the activity lifecycle rules and state transitions.\"\n}\n",
