onHandler. This class is responsible for managing the application's main thread and driving lifecycle transitions by executing the lifecycle-related operations on activities.\\n\\n3. **ActivityRecord.java** (services/core/java/com/android/server/wm/ActivityRecord.java): The server-side representation of an Activity (extends WindowToken). This class runs in the system_server process and tracks the state and properties of activities from the system's perspective, including lifecycle state management.\\n\\n4. **ActivityTaskManagerService.java** (services/core/java/com/android/server/wm/ActivityTaskManagerService.java): The system service (extends IActivityTaskManager.Stub) that manages activity stacks and tasks. It coordinates lifecycle transitions for all activities in the system and enforces the activity lifecycle rules and state transitions.\"\n}\n",
